    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means in Paul's own context and argument. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from the resurrection indicative (3:1-4) through the two clothing-changes (3:5-14), the three reigning realities (3:15-17), and the household code (3:18-25). The structural backbone is the indicative-imperative logic: every command rests on a finished work.",
